Privacy Policy of Kids Workout: Fitness For Kids
Definitions:
To explain this Privacy Policy:
You:
Refers to the person using the service, specifically the parent or guardian of a child under 13 years of age.
Company
(or “We,” “Us,” or “Our”): Refers to Incremental Developer, acting as the provider of the Kids Workout: Fitness For Kids application.
Application:
Refers to the software named Kids Workout: Fitness For Kids.
Service:
Refers to the Kids Workout: Fitness For Kids app.
Device:
Any tool (such as a smartphone or tablet) used to access the Service.
Age Data:
Refers to the user-provided information about the child’s age, used solely to ensure app features comply with applicable family policies and regulations.
——————————————-
Collecting and Using Data:
We respect your privacy and adhere to the Google Play Family Policy.
Personal Data:
*        We do not collect, store, or share any personally identifiable information (such as names, email addresses, or contact details) from users of the Kids Workout: Fitness For Kids app.
Age Data:
*        We ask for the child’s age solely to customize the experience within the app to ensure it is appropriate for the user’s age group.
*        The age data is processed locally on your device and is not transmitted to or stored on any servers.
No Third-Party Sharing:
*        As we do not collect or store any data, there is no sharing of data with third-party companies, advertisers, or analytics services.
Crash Reporting and Analytics:
*        The app may collect non-personal diagnostic data (e.g., crash logs) to improve the app’s functionality and fix issues. This data is anonymous and does not identify any individual user.
———————————————————————
Children’s Privacy:
The Kids Workout: Fitness For Kids app is designed to comply with the Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA) and Google Play’s Family Policy requirements.
*        The app is intended for use by children under the supervision of a parent or guardian.
*        We do not knowingly collect any personal data from children under 13.
If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided personal information by mistake, please contact us immediately at support@incrementaldeveloper.com, and we will take prompt steps to delete such information.
Links to Other Websites:
Our Service may contain links to some other websites that we do not operate. If you click on a third-party link, you will be directed to their site. We recommend you review the privacy policy of every site you visit.
We do not have any control over and take no responsibility for the content, privacy policies, or practices of any third-party services or sites.
Your Privacy Rights:
We value your privacy and are committed to protecting it. As we collect only non-identifiable data, there is no risk of misuse or unauthorized access to your personal information.
Changes to this Privacy Policy:
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page, and the “Last Updated” date will be revised accordingly. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any updates.
Contact Us:
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at support@incrementaldeveloper.com.
We are committed to providing a safe, educational, and fun experience for your children while prioritizing their privacy and security.
